            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="card-title">Key Scientific Evidence Supporting Triadic Interconnectedness</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">The report highlights several lines of evidence. Here are some key examples of interconnectedness:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                    <li><strong>Subatomic:</strong> Theories like Orch-OR and studies on Xenon isotopes hint at quantum processes in consciousness (Psychological Mind $\leftrightarrow$ Philosophical Energies).</li>
                    <li><strong>Atomic/Molecular:</strong> Stress-induced cortisol (Biophysical Substrate) affects mood (Psychological Mind); the gut-brain axis shows digestive health impacting mental states.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cellular:</strong> Bioelectric signals (Philosophical Energies) control cell behavior and morphogenesis (Biophysical Substrate), acting like a "software" layer.</li>
                    <li><strong>Organismic/Interpersonal:</strong> Psychoneuroimmunology shows thoughts/emotions (Psychological Mind) affect immune function (Biophysical Substrate). Social support impacts overall health. The placebo effect demonstrates mind-body healing capacity.</li>
                    <li><strong>Planetary/Cosmic:</strong> Environmental factors like magnetic fields, light, and pollution (Philosophical Energies/Environmental) measurably impact human physiology and mood (Biophysical Substrate/Psychological Mind).</li>
                </ul>
                 <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-slate-500">This evidence underscores that the Triadic Pillars are not just conceptually linked but are supported by observable phenomena across different scales of investigation.</p>
