        <section id="interventions" class="mb-16 pt-16 -mt-16">
            <h2 class="section-title">Multi-Modal Intervention Strategies</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-xl text-lg text-slate-700 space-y-4">
                <p>Psyphibiotriadics proposes comprehensive interventions that address the interconnectedness of the Triadic Pillars. These strategies integrate psychological therapies, physical practices, and energetic modalities to promote homeostasis.</p>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-sky-700 mt-4">Core Approaches:</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Integrated Modalities:</strong> Combining psychological therapies (cognitive regulation, belief systems), physical practices (exercise, yoga, diet), and energetic modalities (biofeedback, meditation).</li>
                    <li><strong>Targeting Imbalances:</strong> Understanding how molecular imbalances (e.g., stress hormones) affect psychological and energetic states to identify precise therapeutic targets. Considering both internal balance and external environmental factors.</li>
                    <li><strong>Leveraging Innate Healing:</strong> Recognizing and intentionally harnessing the placebo effect as a demonstration of the mind's capacity to influence healing. This involves belief- and expectation-driven mechanisms.</li>
